+{"id":"bd-4bit6","title":"Mock/stub finder sweep across fs crates","description":"Apply /mock-code-finder. Sweep all fs crates for stubs/mocks/TODOs/unimplemented!()/todo!()/placeholder strings. File a child bead per finding with file:line and recommended fix. Skip test-only mocks.","notes":"2026-04-27 cod-fs: completed full-crates mock/stub sweep using keyword and AST-short-function scans. Filed production child beads bd-4bit6.1 (btrfs largest contiguous free run stub), bd-4bit6.2 (ext4 write-participating MMP policy/implementation), and bd-4bit6.3 (legacy e2compr algorithm parity/exclusion). Skipped test-only FsOps stubs, fixture placeholder comments, historical ext4 flag descriptions, and local test helper stubs as intentional false positives.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-24T22:22:37.669209777Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:22:45Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T05:22:45Z","close_reason":"Completed mock/stub sweep across fs crates and filed child beads for all actionable production findings; test-only and documentation false positives were intentionally skipped.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-4bit6.1","title":"Implement btrfs largest-contiguous-free-run from extent allocator gaps","description":"Mock/stub sweep finding from crates/ffs-core/src/lib.rs: largest_contiguous_free_run documents btrfs as a stub/conservative upper bound. Replace the total-free-bytes/sector-size fallback with a real largest-free-extent calculation from the btrfs extent allocator/tree state, and add tests covering fragmented vs contiguous free-space layouts. Acceptance: btrfs largest_contiguous_free_run reports the largest allocatable extent, not total free space; statvfs/fallocate planning callers get the corrected value; targeted core tests plus workspace check/clippy pass.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:20:48.178045833Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:20:48.178045833Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","free-space","stub-sweep"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-4bit6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-4bit6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:20:48.178045833Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-4bit6.2","title":"Decide and implement ext4 write-participating MMP behavior","description":"Mock/stub sweep finding from crates/ffs-core/src/lib.rs: validate_ext4_mmp rejects active MMP blocks with 'write-participating MMP is not implemented'. This is a real parity gap for writable ext4 images that use MMP. Decide the correct FrankenFS policy from the ext4 contract: either implement safe write participation/update cadence with tests, or record an explicit exclusion in the parity/spec docs with conformance evidence that active MMP images are intentionally refused. Acceptance: behavior is no longer an undocumented stub string; tests cover clean/fsck/active/unsafe MMP states; FEATURE_PARITY/spec docs match the implemented policy; workspace check/clippy pass.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:21:27.604356420Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:21:27.604356420Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ext4","mmp","stub-sweep"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-4bit6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-4bit6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:21:27.604356420Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-4bit6.3","title":"Resolve legacy e2compr algorithm parity gaps","description":"Mock/stub sweep finding from crates/ffs-core/src/lib.rs: e2compr decompression/compression reports algorithms other than gzip/LZO/none as not implemented (lzv1, lzrw3a, bzip2 legacy formats). Decide whether these are in FrankenFS scope. If in scope, implement readers/writers with fixtures and conformance tests; if out of scope, make the exclusion explicit in PLAN_TO_PORT_FRANKENFS_TO_RUST.md and FEATURE_PARITY.md and keep the runtime error precise. Acceptance: no hidden algorithm gap remains; fixtures cover every supported method and every explicit exclusion; targeted core tests plus workspace check/clippy pass.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:22:04.597214726Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:22:04.597214726Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2compr","ext4","stub-sweep"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-4bit6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-4bit6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:22:04.597214726Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
